transferependuser: title : payment request api
description :
      the payment request api is a standard way for merchants to request payments from consumers. it provides a
      user-friendly interface that allows users to easily complete the payment process. the api supports various payment
      methods, including credit cards, debit cards, and bank accounts, and can be used for both one-time and recurring
      payments. the api also supports multiple currencies and languages, making it a versatile tool for businesses that
      operate in different regions and serve customers from different countries.
endpoints :
    - post /payment-request
      create a payment request
    - get /payment-request/{id}
      get a payment request
    - get /payment-request/{id}/status
      get the status of a payment request
    - get /payment-request/{id}/payment-methods
      get the available payment methods for a payment request
    - post /payment-request/{id}/payment-methods/{paymentmethodid}
      add a payment method to a payment request
    - delete /payment-request/{id}/payment-methods/{paymentmethodid}
      remove a payment method from a payment request
    - post /payment-request/{id}/payment-methods/{paymentmethodid}/payment
      pay with a payment method
    - post /payment-request/{id}/payment-methods/{paymentmethodid}/cancel
      cancel a payment request with a payment method
    - post /payment-request/{id}/payment-methods/{paymentmethodid}/capture
      capture a payment request with a payment method
    - post /payment-request/{id}/payment-methods/{paymentmethodid}/refund
      refund a payment request with a payment method

transferependuser: title : multibanking api
description :
      whole multibanking api
endpoints :
    - get /public/external-banks/connections
      delivers list of external bank connections
    - post /public/external-banks/{bankid}/connections
      (draft) set ups a new ext-bank connection (kbr in mbs context)
    - get /public/external-banks/{bankid}/connections/{connectionid}
      delivers single connection identified by id
    - delete /public/external-banks/{bankid}/connections/{connectionid}
      deletes the ext-bank connection identified by id
    - patch /public/external-banks/{bankid}/connections/{connectionid}
      (draft) updates or replaces kbr data
    - post /public/external-banks/{bankid}/connections/{connectionid}/deactivation
      deactivates the connection with the ext-bank
    - post /public/external-banks/{bankid}/connections/{connectionid}/reactivation
      reactivates the connection with the ext-bank
    - get /public/external-banks/{bankid}/connections/{connectionid}/certificates/{certificateid}
      delivers information related to the certificate
    - get /public/external-banks
      (draft) delivers list of available external-banks, at the moment only those offered via mbs (multibank standard)

user-passwordependuser: title : google identity toolkit
description :
      the google identity toolkit is a set of tools for managing users' identities. it provides a way to authenticate users and authorize their access to your application.
endpoints :
    - get /idp
      get the identity provider (idp) configuration.
    - post /idp
      get an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue
      get an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}
      get an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/refresh
      refresh an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/reissue
      reissue an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/revoke
      revoke an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify
      verify an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}
      verify an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}/info
      get the user information for an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}/info/{key}
      get the value of a user information key for an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}/info/{key}/{value}
      get the key-value pair for an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}/info/{key}/{value}/exists
      check if a key-value pair exists for an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}/info/{key}/{value}/missing
      check if a key-value pair is missing for an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}/info/{key}/{value}/present
      check if a key-value pair is present for an id token from the idp.
    - get /idp/issue/{idtoken}/verify/{idtoken}/info/{key}/{value}/valid

transferependuser: title : bank account api
description :
      this api is used to store and retrieve bank account information for a user. the user can have multiple bank
      accounts associated with them. this api can be used for storing bank account information for multiple purposes
      like creating a transfer or for creating a payment.
endpoints :
    - get /bank_account
      get all the bank accounts associated with the user. this api will return a list of all the bank accounts associated
      with the user.
    - post /bank_account
      add a new bank account associated with the user. this api will add a new bank account associated with the user.
    - get /bank_account/{bank_account_id}
      get a bank account associated with the user. this api will return a bank account associated with the user based on
      the bank account id.
    - put /bank_account/{bank_account_id}

      the customers api allows you to create, retrieve, update, and delete customers. you can also retrieve the customer's
      address book, and retrieve and update the customer's payment information.
endpoints :
    - get /customers
      get list of customers.
    - get /customers/{customerid}
      get customer by id.
    - post /customers
      create customer.
    - put /customers/{customerid}
      update customer.
    - delete /customers/{customerid}
      delete customer.
    - get /customers/{customerid}/addresses
      get customer addresses.
    - get /customers/{customerid}/paymentmethods
      get customer payment methods.
    - get /customers/{customerid}/paymentmethods/{paymentmethodid}
      get customer payment method.
    - put /customers/{customerid}/paymentmethods/{paymentmethodid}
      update customer payment method.
    - delete /customers/{customerid}/paymentmethods/{paymentmethodid}
      delete customer payment method.
    - post /customers/{customerid}/paymentmethods
      create customer payment method.

description :
      a set of api endpoints that allow you to store payment details, confirm, or decline a payment.  for more
      information, refer to [online payments](https://docs.adyen.com/online-payments/online-payments). ## authentication
      to use the pay api, you need to have [two api credentials](https://docs.adyen.com/online-payments/online-payments#payouts-to-bank-accounts-and-wallets): one for storing payment details and submitting payments, and another one for confirming or declining payments. if you don't have the required api credentials, contact our [support team](https://www.adyen.help/hc/en-us/requests/new).  if using an api key, add an `x-api-key` header with [...]
endpoints :
    - post /confirmthirdparty
      confirm a payment
    - post /declinethirdparty
      cancel a payment
    - post /payment
      make an instant card payment
    - post /storedetail
      store payment details
    - post /storedetailandsubmitthirdparty
      store details and submit a payment
    - post /submitthirdparty
      submit a payment
